title: Investigation of excitation functions of alpha induced reactions on natXe: Production of the therapeutic radioisotope 131Cs

reactions on natXe: Production of the therapeutic
radioisotope 131Cs

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nucl. Instrum. Methods in Physics Res., Sect.B, Vol.267, p.742 (2009)

x4freetext: CGR-560 cyclotron
Stainless steel gas cells (diam: 2 cm, length: 2.5 cm)
having 25 micron polyimid film windows
filled with high purity Xe gas
(99.99%, natural isotopic composition),
gas pressure: 1.3 bars
Incident alpha energies: 45, 36, 32 and 26 MeV,
beam currents: 100 nA.
The energy of the primary beam was obtained from
cyclotron settings, calibrated in a separate
experiment.
Four gascells were stacked in a closed metal cylinder
serving as a holder and Faraday-cup for the
preliminary beam current measurement.
The produced activities were assessed nondestructively
i.e. the irradiated cells were placed without any
treatment at large sample-detector distances.
The first measurements were done immediately after
the end of bombardment while the second set was
started about 2 h later.
Ti foils, thickness: 20 micron

x4freetext: Volume 4
The energy of the particles at the mid-plane of the
irradiated cells was determined by calculation of the
energy degradation.
Decay data were taken from NuDat database.
The uncertainty on the particle energy was
estimated taking into account the uncertainties on the
energy of the primary beam, the uncertainty on the
thicknesses of the different stopping media in the
stack, the fluctuations of the gas target density and
the energy straggling. The uncertainty on the energy
varies between 0.3 and 1.0 MeV.
The uncertainties were estimated in the
standard way: the independent relative errors of the
linearly contributing processes:
* number of the bombarding particles,
*  number of the target nuclei,
*  decay data,
*  detector efficiency and
*  peak area)
were summed quadratically and the square root of the
sum was taken. The uncertainties on the absolute cross
sections were estimated to be 12-20%.
The measured experimental data were compared to
and analyzed with theoretical calculations based on
the model code ALICE-IPPE.
On the basis of the new experimental cross
sections integral yields were calculated.

The production cross section for 129mBa is relative
since only relative intensities were found in the
literature for gamma lines following the decay of the
metastable state.
